.SH ENVIRONMENT
.IP DISPLAY
The default display to be used.
.IP WISH_CMD
This variable allows you to select a different interpreter
(something else than in the xf script).
.IP WISH_TEST_CMD
This variable allows you to select a different interpreter
for testing (something else than in the xf script).
.IP XF_DIR
This variable sets the xf toplevel directory to the given
value.
.IP XF_ADD_DIR
This option sets the xf additionals directory to the given
value. This directory contains widget sources of the widgets
that are not part of the core Tk distribution, like the
Hypertext widget. The parameter can be a list of pathnames
separated by ':'.
.IP XF_APP_FILE
This variable sets the xf application default file to the
given value. This file contains application defaults for xf.
.IP XF_BIND_FILE
This variable sets the xf binding file to the given value.
This file contains the class bindings of the widgets, and
procedures that are needed by the bindings.
.IP XF_COLOR_FILE
This variable sets the xf color file to the given value.
This file contains the names and values of the known colors.
.IP XF_CONFIG_FILE
This variable sets the xf configuration file to the given
value. This file contains the settings of xf. If a
configuration file is specified, all other commandline
settings are ignored.
.IP XF_CURSOR_FILE
This variable sets the xf cursor file to the given value.
This file contains the names of the known cursors.
.IP XF_ELEM_DIR
This variable sets the xf element directory to the given
value. This directory contains the widget sources of the
widgets that are part of the core Tk distribution.
.IP XF_FONT_FILE
This variable sets the xf font file to the given value. This
file contains the names of the known fonts.
.IP XF_HELP_DIR
This option sets the xf help directory to the given value.
This directory contains the help pages for xf. The parameter
can be a list of pathnames separated by ':'.
.IP XF_ICONBAR_FILE
This variable sets the xf iconbar file to the given value.
This file contains the definition of the iconbar.
.IP XF_ICONS_DIR
This option sets the xf icon directory to the given value.
This directory contains the icons for the iconbar. The
parameter can be a list of pathnames separated by ':'.
.IP XF_KEYSYM_FILE
This variable sets the xf keysyms file to the given value.
This file contains the names of the known keysyms.
.IP XF_LIB_DIR
This variable sets the xf library directory to the given
value. This directory contains the font-, color-, cursor-
and keysym-files.
.IP XF_MENUBAR_FILE
This variable sets the xf menubar file to the given value.
This file contains the definition of the menubar.
.IP XF_POS_FILE
This variable sets the xf position file to the given value.
This file contains the positions of the windows.
.IP XF_PROC_DIR
This variable sets the xf procedure directory to the given
value. This directory contains the version archive of the
procedures. Procedures can be stored with the shape toolkit
(available at ftp.cs.tu-berlin.de).
.IP XF_SRC_DIR
This variable sets the xf source directory to the given
value. This directory contains the complete sources of xf.
.IP XF_TMPLT_DIR
This variable sets the xf template directory to the given
value. This directory contains the source templates. You can
use templates to create complex interface elements that are
used repeatedly in your applications. These elements can be
stored permanently. The parameter can be a list of pathnames
separated by ':'.
.IP XF_TMP_DIR
This variable sets the xf temporary directory to the given
value. This directory contains temporary files.
.IP XF_UNIQUE_ID
This variable sets the unique id for xf. Each running xf
that accesses the same file system as the other running xf,
and does not use a local directory for temporary data should
have a unique id. If this variable is not set, xf will
create an id by itself. This variable is intended for these
machines that have trouble with this id creation mechanism.
.PP

